The '''Krevaaki''' were a [[Species/Legends|race]] of [[Sentience/Legends|sentients]] native to [[Krevas]]. The Krevaaki people possessed an [[exoskeleton]].<ref name="The Unknown Regions" /> The face of a Krevaaki was composed of a series of shifting, [[Chitin/Legends|chitinous]] plates with a limited range of expression. During face-to-face communication, it was difficult for anyone who was not a Krevaaki to read their facial expressions.

Krevaaki used their tentacles instead of [[Limb/Legends|arms]] and legs like bipeds. They often concealed the true number from [[Humanoid/Legends|humanoids]].

==Biology and appearance==
Descended from shallow-water crustaceans, Krevaaki were sizable non-humanoids. From youth, they trained their tentacles for specific purposes. Older individuals became less adaptable. Over millennia, they had evolved to technology.

When excited, a Krevaaki's musk would smell.<ref name="ItV">''[[Dawn of the Jedi: Into the Void]]''</ref>

==History==
Even in the fabled [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Old Republic]], Krevaaki were made conscious of their appearance. Great explorers in times of peace, they sought to avoid conflict. Large groups were never found away from their homeworld, off the [[Perlemian Trade Route/Legends|Perlemian Trade Route]].

==Society and culture==
The species dedicated themselves to spiritual experience. Not violent or materialistic, they stayed out of the affairs of others.

==Krevaaki in the galaxy==
One Krevaaki, [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Master]] [[Vodo-Siosk Baas]], trained [[Exar Kun/Legends|Exar Kun]] as his [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] [[Padawan/Legends|Padawan]]. Other Krevaaki included Baas's descendent [[Bodo Baas]]<ref name="EGTTF">[[Jedi vs. Sith: The Essential Guide to the Force (real-life book)|''Jedi vs. Sith: The Essential Guide to the Force'']]</ref> and [[Saaj Calician]], a [[Sith Lord/Legends|Sith Lord]] who was active during the [[Republic Dark Age]].<ref name="Knight Errant novel">[[Knight Errant (novel)|''Knight Errant'']]</ref>

